WEBVTT

00:10.492 --> 00:12.797
<i>Previously on</i>
Hap and Leonard

00:12.823 --> 00:14.289
Florida's car.

00:16.039 --> 00:17.594
<i>How many dead bodies you seen?</i>

00:17.804 --> 00:20.171
Enough to know
this man didn't kill himself.

00:20.197 --> 00:21.289
Here you are again

00:21.315 --> 00:22.344
in my seat.

00:22.370 --> 00:25.487
Federal law prohibate from
discriminatin' on the basis of race.

00:25.513 --> 00:27.503
- This is my town.
- What that got to do with me?

00:27.529 --> 00:29.261
You ain't above the law
is what I'm saying.

00:29.287 --> 00:32.215
'Till I know for sure she dead,
she ain't dead.

00:32.926 --> 00:34.027
Stop it.

00:34.184 --> 00:35.387
<i>Let go.</i>

00:43.083 --> 00:45.786
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

00:45.820 --> 00:48.824
♪♪

00:55.830 --> 00:58.834
♪♪

01:00.000 --> 01:06.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:08.575 --> 01:09.541
[GASPS]

01:09.567 --> 01:10.577
Holy shit.

01:11.679 --> 01:12.714
Florida?

01:13.714 --> 01:16.717
♪♪

01:22.355 --> 01:23.635
[WHISPERS] Come on.

01:26.159 --> 01:28.562
[CAR DOOR CREAKS]
Florida?

01:29.596 --> 01:32.132
♪♪

01:33.397 --> 01:34.660
[HUFFS]

01:35.090 --> 01:36.138
Where you been?

01:36.559 --> 01:38.114
We've been looking everywhere for you.

01:38.220 --> 01:39.301
Shh.

01:40.942 --> 01:41.871
[WHISPERS] Leonard.

01:43.626 --> 01:44.961
[CAR DOOR CREAKS CLOSED]

01:48.242 --> 01:49.387
Come with me, Hap.

01:50.325 --> 01:51.343
Come on.

01:52.330 --> 01:53.737
Where are we goin'?

01:55.563 --> 01:56.645
Hap!

01:56.956 --> 01:58.325
- Hap!
- [SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY]

01:58.786 --> 02:00.173
Get the hell off me!
[FROGS RIBBITING]

02:00.208 --> 02:02.226
Hap! Hap!

02:02.538 --> 02:03.973
Hap, help! Help!

02:04.006 --> 02:06.075
- I can't, Leonard!
- Hap!

02:06.568 --> 02:09.143
- I c... I can't move!
- Hap, help me!

02:09.175 --> 02:11.640
[RIBBITING CONTINUES]
Hap!

02:12.313 --> 02:13.315
Leonard!

02:14.428 --> 02:15.963
-Ah! [GROANS]
- What? What?

02:16.035 --> 02:17.604
- Oh! No. No.
- You... you say somethin'?

02:17.630 --> 02:18.851
- No. No.
- Oh, shit!

02:18.877 --> 02:19.811
Wh... Aah!

02:19.844 --> 02:21.847
♪♪

02:22.981 --> 02:24.817
[CREDITS]

02:50.247 --> 02:52.637
S03E05
<i>Mambo #5</i>

02:54.590 --> 02:57.035
Sync and correction by LittleDuck
www.addic7ed.com

02:59.148 --> 03:02.700
Miss, where'd you get
this lipstick tube from?

03:03.718 --> 03:06.862
Lady it belongs to,
you know where she is?

03:08.340 --> 03:10.426
Uh, her name is Florida Grange,

03:10.459 --> 03:12.387
and, um, we've been lookin'
for her, see, so...

03:12.867 --> 03:14.075
You seen her?

03:14.495 --> 03:16.129
♪♪

03:19.700 --> 03:21.505
I can't get her to speak.

03:21.834 --> 03:24.501
She hasn't said a damn word in years.

03:26.946 --> 03:28.265
Young lady,

03:29.090 --> 03:31.641
if you do have the power of speech,

03:32.679 --> 03:35.239
now would be
a real good time to use it.

03:35.815 --> 03:37.484
♪♪

03:39.593 --> 03:41.075
All right, step aside.

03:41.101 --> 03:42.819
Why? What you gonna do
that's any different?

03:42.845 --> 03:44.705
Easy, that's done no worse than
what you're doing right now.

03:44.731 --> 03:47.311
- All right, you just go ahead, then.
- I'm goin'.

03:52.470 --> 03:55.096
Oh, come on now. What?
Charades? Are you kiddin'?

03:55.313 --> 03:57.147
She ain't deaf, Leonard.

03:59.092 --> 04:01.558
Ah! Ha! Look like we speak
the same language.

04:01.987 --> 04:03.258
[THUNDER RUMBLING]
No, no,

04:03.292 --> 04:05.294
she just knows that's
Florida's car and that's it.

04:05.328 --> 04:07.358
Come on, man, we... we gotta
get outta here.

04:07.384 --> 04:08.577
All right, hold on, now.

04:10.749 --> 04:12.638
You know how to get us outta here?

04:16.939 --> 04:18.406
I'm just good at this.

04:18.440 --> 04:19.776
- No, no.
- Admit it.

04:19.809 --> 04:21.695
Oh, oh, oh. You're just
lucky, that's all.

04:22.560 --> 04:23.912
HAP: If we'd
still been together,

04:23.946 --> 04:27.137
I could've talked her out
of going to Grovetown.

04:27.393 --> 04:28.725
Ain't your fault, Hap.

04:29.264 --> 04:31.954
White folk been killin' black folk
around here for years now.

04:32.334 --> 04:34.897
Not everything you think
is your fault, is your fault.

04:35.399 --> 04:38.293
Yeah, maybe 90%.
The rest just chalk it up.

04:38.327 --> 04:40.730
- 90%?
- All right, maybe 95.

04:40.762 --> 04:43.256
Look, it happens in life.
Shit happens now.

04:43.491 --> 04:45.760
Let me tell you a story
about when I was in Nam.

04:45.903 --> 04:47.928
Me and my platoon, we got
stuck in this rice paddy.

04:47.970 --> 04:49.906
- Hot as a goddamn sauna.
- Mm-hmm.

04:49.939 --> 04:51.374
Stand up, bullet in the head.

04:51.406 --> 04:53.342
Sit down, leeches crawl up your ass.

04:53.562 --> 04:56.342
Got so bad, we had to
call in that steel rain.

04:58.038 --> 04:59.592
I ain't gonna lie to you.

04:59.814 --> 05:02.794
When that thing came down out
the sky, I was scared as shit.

05:03.380 --> 05:06.834
Kid next to me took one
in the neck, blood everywhere.

05:07.879 --> 05:09.263
Started crying.

05:11.294 --> 05:14.814
Then I picked him up,
carried him on my shoulder,

05:15.241 --> 05:19.083
through all that shrapnel,
thick as the goddamn flies.

05:21.935 --> 05:25.850
About a half-mile in,
I-I could've sworn I felt

05:25.876 --> 05:28.823
- my heart beating through my chest.
- Yeah.

05:29.267 --> 05:30.464
And it just stopped.

05:32.010 --> 05:35.025
And that's when I realized,
it wasn't mine, it was his.

05:35.795 --> 05:36.915
Whoa.

05:37.085 --> 05:39.094
So what... what'd you do?

05:40.154 --> 05:41.542
I kept goin',

05:42.428 --> 05:45.126
'cause dead or alive,
I was gettin' him home.

05:46.239 --> 05:47.445
Ah.

05:48.549 --> 05:49.577
Okay.

05:50.811 --> 05:52.246
Dead or alive,

05:52.662 --> 05:54.132
Florida's coming home.

05:55.638 --> 05:58.642
♪♪

06:03.212 --> 06:05.545
[VEHICLE APPROACHING]

06:09.051 --> 06:11.637
Whoa, shit! Shit! Back.

06:12.254 --> 06:14.342
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

06:25.425 --> 06:28.329
Y'all can come on out.
We seen ya down the road.

06:28.355 --> 06:30.775
[PETE LAUGHING]
[ENGINE TURNS OFF, DOOR OPENS]

06:34.744 --> 06:38.195
Heard you two started some
trouble over there in Grovetown.

06:38.221 --> 06:39.816
[LAUGHS]

06:40.116 --> 06:41.951
Call people tryin' to kill you trouble.

06:42.231 --> 06:45.388
Well, we told you they was
gonna <i> love</i> you in Grovetown.

06:45.420 --> 06:47.118
- Didn't we, Pete?
- Mm.

06:47.754 --> 06:49.124
We're outta gas.

06:49.992 --> 06:51.498
Can we have some?

06:52.128 --> 06:53.825
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

06:54.590 --> 06:58.053
[GASOLINE TRICKLING]

06:58.633 --> 07:01.498
PETE: That should be enough
to get you to a gas station.

07:01.889 --> 07:03.673
Y'all know where
the nearest phone might be?

07:03.705 --> 07:05.926
Well, with that storm comin'
from up north,

07:05.952 --> 07:07.949
lines up there be down.

07:08.443 --> 07:11.280
[SIGHS] I'd say the nearest
phone would be Grovetown.

07:11.314 --> 07:13.383
Ohh. Grovetown, huh?

07:13.415 --> 07:14.750
You two listen up.

07:14.783 --> 07:17.153
I'm-a suggest you get in
your car and drive as fast

07:17.186 --> 07:19.131
and as far as that gas'll take ya.

07:19.278 --> 07:21.341
Anywhere but Grovetown.

07:21.857 --> 07:24.631
Well, sir, we aim to finish
what we started.

07:24.715 --> 07:26.022
And then some.

07:26.150 --> 07:29.621
Son, you ever heard of man
named Ebner Flautt?

07:30.263 --> 07:31.665
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

07:31.691 --> 07:33.419
No, ma'am, can't say that I have.

07:33.663 --> 07:36.709
You know why you ain't never
heard of Ebner Flautt?

07:37.047 --> 07:38.402
No, ma'am.

07:38.497 --> 07:41.168
'Cause he ain't had the sense
God gave a billy goat.

07:41.194 --> 07:43.674
Not the sharpest knife in the drawer.

07:44.764 --> 07:46.238
So...
[BOTTLES CLINK]

07:46.995 --> 07:49.158
what happened to Ebner Flautt?

07:50.777 --> 07:52.227
No idea.

07:52.769 --> 07:54.194
None.

07:56.242 --> 07:59.278
[MYSTERIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

08:00.694 --> 08:04.006
Yes, ma'am. I understand now.

08:04.716 --> 08:06.675
♪♪

08:09.115 --> 08:11.038
Come on, Belinda.
Get in the car, baby.

08:11.064 --> 08:12.600
We gonna take you home.

08:12.655 --> 08:14.131
Y'all better get to hoppin'.

08:14.157 --> 08:16.059
[DOOR CLOSES, ENGINE STARTS]

08:16.085 --> 08:19.322
[METALLIC RATTLING]

08:21.364 --> 08:23.052
Did I just miss somethin'?

08:23.333 --> 08:26.002
Oh, Uncle Chester used to
do the same damn thing,

08:26.035 --> 08:28.426
tell a story didn't make no sense.

08:28.972 --> 08:31.908
Till one day, I'd be dodging
one of his ass whoopins,

08:31.941 --> 08:34.195
runnin' through the house,
and it would hit me.

08:34.662 --> 08:36.061
That's what he meant.

08:37.163 --> 08:38.530
What did she mean?

08:38.556 --> 08:40.681
When I figure it out,
I'll let you know.

08:40.783 --> 08:43.909
Just tell Gil Sweeney, get his
tractor over to Trotter's farm.

08:43.936 --> 08:45.455
We're filling sandbags over there

08:45.489 --> 08:47.123
and we need all the help we can get.

08:47.157 --> 08:49.159
Come on! [GROANS]

08:49.193 --> 08:50.197
Reynolds... Reynolds!

08:50.233 --> 08:52.210
Reynolds! God, ah! Reynolds!

08:53.031 --> 08:54.266
Power and phones are out

08:54.292 --> 08:55.968
over in North Riverside neighborhood.

08:56.132 --> 08:58.788
Get on over and get them
folks evacuated.

08:59.402 --> 09:01.530
[DOOR CREAKING CLOSED]

09:02.037 --> 09:03.905
Hey, you better loosen them pants, son.

09:03.938 --> 09:05.444
You look like you're about
to pop a gasket.

09:05.470 --> 09:08.006
Lucas Hobbs saw
Florida Grange's Volvo on the highway.

09:08.405 --> 09:11.358
- Two men inside headed into town.
- Where you going?

09:11.407 --> 09:12.582
- After them.
- Who?

09:12.608 --> 09:14.508
- Collins and Pine.
- How do you know it's them?

09:14.534 --> 09:15.616
Who else would it be?

09:15.642 --> 09:17.395
And what are you gonna
go ahead 'em for?

09:17.421 --> 09:18.956
For driving a Volvo?

09:18.989 --> 09:21.181
We're not in the babysitting
business, Officer.

09:21.207 --> 09:22.631
We got more important things to do

09:22.657 --> 09:25.079
than them two busted flushes,
which is why you're on your way

09:25.111 --> 09:28.622
out that door,
headed over to North Riverside.

09:30.093 --> 09:31.181
Yes, sir.

09:31.390 --> 09:33.803
God diggity damn dog.

09:34.693 --> 09:37.499
Why do people have
to make my job so hard?

09:38.296 --> 09:40.035
I'm busy as shit.

09:40.163 --> 09:41.910
Got a storm crawling up my ass.

09:41.936 --> 09:45.056
Got a set of balls can't
be tamed by liquid barometer.

09:45.241 --> 09:47.163
And now here you are, telling me

09:47.189 --> 09:49.658
these two cartoon characters
are back here.

09:49.773 --> 09:51.208
Do you want me to find 'em?

09:51.241 --> 09:52.934
Hell, yes, I want you to find them.

09:52.960 --> 09:55.301
And when you do, I want you
to get them over to Trotter's farm,

09:55.327 --> 09:57.151
want you to get 'em busy
filling sandbags.

09:57.186 --> 09:59.028
But you see Truman Brown
anywhere near them,

09:59.054 --> 10:01.366
or them him, you call me.

10:01.680 --> 10:02.764
Yes, sir.

10:04.998 --> 10:07.170
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

10:08.288 --> 10:10.452
- Grovetown Police.
- WOMAN: <i> Yes, this is Miss Loretta...</i>

10:10.478 --> 10:12.514
Ah. Oh.
<i>[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]</i>

10:12.649 --> 10:15.620
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

10:15.952 --> 10:17.958
[MACHINE WHIRRING]

10:18.820 --> 10:20.389
[WHIRRING STOPS]

10:20.423 --> 10:22.692
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

10:22.725 --> 10:24.218
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

10:24.958 --> 10:26.627
Look like Hanson's car.

10:26.632 --> 10:27.683
Yeah.

10:27.709 --> 10:29.445
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]
HAP: Where the hell is Hanson?

10:29.902 --> 10:31.504
TIM: Hey, look who's back.

10:31.537 --> 10:33.528
You boys need a room for the night?

10:33.554 --> 10:36.725
Gonna be a mighty nasty storm.
Be a good idea to wait it out.

10:37.042 --> 10:38.911
Hey, that's, uh, that lawyer lady's car.

10:38.945 --> 10:41.446
- You find her?
- No. Not yet.

10:41.498 --> 10:43.100
Where'd you tow this in from?

10:43.256 --> 10:45.312
Craziest thing, got a call
from highway patrol.

10:45.338 --> 10:46.673
They found the car in a ditch

10:46.704 --> 10:48.473
with tarp wrapped around the windshield.

10:48.499 --> 10:49.600
Hey.

10:50.507 --> 10:51.836
Where's the driver?

10:52.377 --> 10:56.114
Mm. Could be anywhere.
Or nowhere.

10:56.486 --> 10:59.185
Black folk just dropping dead
like flies around here, huh?

11:01.327 --> 11:04.651
I gotta call Charlie.
Can I use your phone, Tim?

11:04.856 --> 11:06.149
Ohh.
[SIGHS]

11:06.175 --> 11:08.310
- Oh, let me guess... line's dead.
- Yeah, yeah.

11:08.603 --> 11:11.773
Uh, Maude's Diner phone made it
through the past two hurricanes.

11:12.483 --> 11:14.359
Means we gotta go back to Grovetown.

11:14.385 --> 11:15.927
- Shit.
- Mm.

11:16.587 --> 11:18.975
Say, you ain't get a call to
pick up the El Camino, did ya?

11:19.001 --> 11:20.038
No.

11:20.380 --> 11:21.578
Means no guns.

11:21.604 --> 11:24.452
No. So we gotta just...
[INHALES DEEPLY]

11:24.641 --> 11:26.275
be on our best behavior.

11:26.676 --> 11:29.646
[THUNDER CRASHES]
[DOG BARKING]

11:29.680 --> 11:32.650
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

11:32.683 --> 11:35.178
♪♪

11:38.756 --> 11:41.257
We need to use the phone,
if it's workin'.

11:41.290 --> 11:44.527
- It's working.
- Just one call, then we're done.

11:44.995 --> 11:46.597
<i>Caller number 15...</i>

11:46.630 --> 11:47.830
Come on in.

11:48.232 --> 11:50.800
<i>...sweet potato pie
from Maude's Diner</i>

11:50.833 --> 11:53.618
<i>in beautiful downtown Grovetown.</i>

11:53.804 --> 11:56.940
- <i>1990 is just 'round the corner.</i>
- Y'all, dig in.

11:56.973 --> 11:58.508
Might be your last supper for a while

11:58.541 --> 11:59.877
- with this storm comin'.
- MAN: Oh.

11:59.910 --> 12:01.444
- WOMAN: Ah.
- You know what I'm sayin'?

12:01.478 --> 12:02.813
[BACK DOOR CLOSES]

12:02.846 --> 12:05.699
- <i>Get 'em early.</i>
- Shit. That's all I need.

12:06.016 --> 12:09.417
<i>The storm's rollin', rollin',
rollin' into Grovetown.</i>

12:09.443 --> 12:10.894
MAN: Look who's back.

12:10.920 --> 12:13.062
<i>This next song goes out
to Sue Ann Nevil...</i>

12:13.171 --> 12:14.929
<i>"What Will the New Year Bring?"</i>

12:15.174 --> 12:18.244
...could not follow a recipe
if her life depended on it.

12:18.811 --> 12:20.653
Way too salty and dry.

12:21.070 --> 12:23.856
Well, then Debra Ann brought
her cornbread stuffing.

12:23.882 --> 12:26.194
- Yes, she did.
- Excuse me, ma'am.

12:26.220 --> 12:28.077
[BELL JINGLES]
Are... are you gonna be long?

12:28.413 --> 12:30.496
Uh, could you hold on
just a second, Mama?

12:30.522 --> 12:32.373
See, I got an emergency.

12:32.678 --> 12:34.906
I am talkin' to my mother!

12:34.932 --> 12:36.067
[DOOR THUDS]

12:36.583 --> 12:37.639
WOMAN: Mm-hmm.

12:37.665 --> 12:39.569
Wait. Let me try something.
[CLEARS THROAT]

12:39.663 --> 12:41.689
- WOMAN: Yes.
- Ma'am...

12:42.803 --> 12:45.834
Anybody ever have
the good sense of tellin' you,

12:45.968 --> 12:48.984
you have the most bewitchin' eyes?

12:49.798 --> 12:52.043
Cut the crap and wait your turn.

12:52.076 --> 12:53.411
[DOOR THUDS]
Mama...

12:53.443 --> 12:56.061
When you gonna realize
you're black by association?

12:56.346 --> 12:58.783
[WOMAN LAUGHS]

12:58.815 --> 13:01.651
[DOOR THUDS]
Mama, she gon' call you back.

13:01.684 --> 13:03.092
[CALL DISCONNECTS]

13:03.118 --> 13:04.311
Well, I never!

13:04.337 --> 13:06.405
And you ain't never gonna
neither. Now git.

13:07.392 --> 13:09.760
[BLUESY ROCK SONG
PLAYING IN BACKGROUND]

13:09.793 --> 13:11.314
♪♪

13:12.195 --> 13:15.444
[COIN CLINKS, ROTARY DIAL WHIRRING]

13:16.587 --> 13:18.202
- PEG: <i> Laborde Sheriff's Department.</i>
- Hey, Peg.

13:18.235 --> 13:21.019
It's Hap Collins here.
I gotta talk to Charlie Blank.

13:21.045 --> 13:23.147
Hap Collins!

13:23.173 --> 13:24.738
- It's urgent.
- <i>[CHUCKLES] Hey.</i>

13:24.764 --> 13:27.724
I missed you and Leonard
at the Toys for Tots event

13:27.758 --> 13:29.591
<i>on Christmas Day.</i>
[TIRES SCREECHING]

13:30.388 --> 13:32.149
- Yeah, Peg.
- Shit.

13:32.263 --> 13:33.355
Peg?

13:33.635 --> 13:35.370
[ENGINE REVS, BRAKES SQUEAL]
Peg, it's an emergency!

13:35.599 --> 13:37.468
I gotta speak to Charlie Blank now.

13:37.500 --> 13:40.178
<i>Listen now, Raynell made...</i>

13:40.204 --> 13:41.846
Looks like we're gonna
close early.

13:41.872 --> 13:44.474
- <i>Peg, I gotta speak to Charlie Blank</i>.
- ...you know, with all the toasted tips

13:44.508 --> 13:45.910
<i>off the whip black of the ocean.</i>

13:45.942 --> 13:47.644
<i>And you know that little girl last year</i>

13:47.677 --> 13:49.147
<i>that puked up on Leonard?</i>

13:49.180 --> 13:51.258
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

13:54.417 --> 13:56.253
MAN: What's up, boys?

13:58.021 --> 14:00.370
♪♪

14:08.530 --> 14:09.908
Howdy, boys.

14:10.401 --> 14:12.637
♪♪

14:12.997 --> 14:15.676
<i>Hello? You still there? Hap?</i>

14:17.940 --> 14:19.812
MAN: Come on, let's go.
[DOOR OPENS]

14:20.477 --> 14:22.446
I thought you boys
would've been gone by now.

14:22.642 --> 14:25.664
- Excuse me.
- Oh. Yes, ma'am.

14:28.532 --> 14:31.276
You brought this on yourselves.

14:34.485 --> 14:37.161
They're just using the phone,
Truman, then leavin'.

14:37.662 --> 14:39.129
[DOOR CLOSES]
No, Maude.

14:39.155 --> 14:41.958
No, I'd like to get a table,
get something to eat.

14:41.984 --> 14:43.875
And Leonard, too,
so we're gonna need

14:43.901 --> 14:46.503
two turkey clubs, fries, and a drink.

14:46.536 --> 14:48.238
