30:29.027 --> 30:30.868
and got me a scholarship.

30:31.368 --> 30:34.083
Studied hard to be
a veterinarian.

30:34.311 --> 30:35.849
Moved to Chicago.

30:37.714 --> 30:39.516
Big city life.

30:41.152 --> 30:42.654
Then I moved back down here.

30:42.946 --> 30:45.696
I realized that what I learned
was much more beneficial

30:45.722 --> 30:49.092
for the people of the Southside,
and these Grovetown doctors

30:49.125 --> 30:51.762
were giving diabetics
a jar full of aspirin

30:51.796 --> 30:55.181
and charging them $75,
which they could not pay.

30:55.799 --> 30:58.735
So... I stepped up.

30:59.106 --> 31:01.834
Used what I learned,
taught myself more,

31:02.602 --> 31:04.129
and helped the people.

31:06.109 --> 31:08.087
Mm, Maude...

31:08.873 --> 31:12.326
well, she made it possible
for me to earn a living.

31:14.085 --> 31:15.519
And then

31:16.232 --> 31:17.321
I stay here,

31:17.708 --> 31:20.980
where I can do some good,
where I'm needed.

31:23.674 --> 31:25.457
Get you some rest, hear?

31:26.172 --> 31:27.758
[WHISPERS] Thank you.

31:32.068 --> 31:34.673
[GRUNTS SOFTLY]

31:35.368 --> 31:37.220
CANTUCK OVER RADIO: <i>
What the hell happened, Sneed?</i>

31:37.246 --> 31:38.915
It was Truman Brown and his boys.

31:39.449 --> 31:42.218
<i>They tore up Maude's place
and beat these boys up good.</i>

31:42.250 --> 31:44.417
- Oh, shit.
- We need to get him to a doctor.

31:44.443 --> 31:46.346
Does Brown know they're
holed up at Bacon's?

31:46.372 --> 31:47.833
I don't think so.

31:48.780 --> 31:51.149
Bacon knows what he's doing.
Best they stay out there.

31:51.181 --> 31:53.651
<i>And until I get there, you stay put.</i>

31:53.685 --> 31:56.588
<i>- Do you hear me, Sneed?
- Yes, sir.</i>

31:56.621 --> 31:59.624
♪♪

32:06.630 --> 32:08.166
[BRAKES SQUEAL]

32:08.198 --> 32:09.601
[ENGINE TURNS OFF]

32:15.253 --> 32:16.938
Got a little present for ya.

32:16.964 --> 32:19.980
Figure you didn't have me
drive all the way out here for nothin'.

32:20.006 --> 32:22.679
Those boys from Laborde,
they're out at Bacon's house.

32:22.824 --> 32:24.463
Sneed's with 'em.

32:24.886 --> 32:25.933
Good.

32:27.482 --> 32:29.007
You gonna be home later?

32:29.348 --> 32:31.988
Why, yes, ma'am, I believe I will be.

32:33.319 --> 32:34.911
I'll bring the pie.

32:35.354 --> 32:38.358
♪♪

32:45.364 --> 32:47.042
♪♪

32:48.372 --> 32:50.074
[GRUNTS]

32:51.505 --> 32:53.229
Oh, damn, that one hurts.

32:53.255 --> 32:54.687
If you don't stop fidgeting...
[GROANS]

32:54.713 --> 32:56.242
it's gonna hurt more.
[FRONT DOOR OPENS]

32:56.268 --> 32:58.837
[GRUNTS, PANTING]
[FRONT DOOR CLOSES]

32:59.328 --> 33:00.815
- Hey, Sneed.
- Hmm?

33:01.638 --> 33:03.282
We found Florida's car

33:03.811 --> 33:06.792
over at Truman Brown's place.

33:08.131 --> 33:09.613
Chief looked into it,

33:09.801 --> 33:11.617
and Truman Brown didn't kill her.

33:11.967 --> 33:13.469
At least not out there.

33:13.605 --> 33:17.343
Yeah, well, I'm supposed
to trust the Chief, huh?

33:18.113 --> 33:20.087
You think it's easy
keepin' the peace around here?

33:20.113 --> 33:23.182
No, I don't think it's easy
keeping the damn peace anywhere.

33:23.214 --> 33:26.496
But that don't mean to say
I'm gonna trust Cantuck.

33:26.673 --> 33:27.914
He's a good man.

33:27.940 --> 33:29.609
Yeah, you tell that
to Bobby Joe Soothe...

33:29.642 --> 33:31.411
- Mm.
- and Florida.

33:31.437 --> 33:33.072
He wants to find out what
happened to them

33:33.106 --> 33:34.777
- much as you do.
- Yeah?

33:34.840 --> 33:37.878
Yeah, well, maybe he should've
asked for some help, huh?

33:38.371 --> 33:40.785
You know, instead of
kicking us out of town.

33:40.811 --> 33:43.548
- You should've left!
- I <i> will</i> leave

33:43.637 --> 33:45.489
when I find Florida.

33:45.603 --> 33:47.616
Not that you give a damn about her.

33:47.642 --> 33:50.348
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

33:53.213 --> 33:55.222
My father died in prison.

33:55.884 --> 33:57.449
Did you know that, Collins?

33:59.533 --> 34:01.067
When I was 14.

34:01.745 --> 34:04.715
He killed a man for
stealing tools out of our shed.

34:05.539 --> 34:06.823
A black man.

34:11.098 --> 34:12.942
It's no excuse, just...

34:13.878 --> 34:15.335
Just get off your goddamn high horse

34:15.370 --> 34:17.331
for once in your life, Collins.

34:18.318 --> 34:19.748
BACON: Sneed's right.

34:20.007 --> 34:21.342
[HAP GRUNTS]
You should've left.

34:21.375 --> 34:23.744
- Yeah.
- Now look at yourself, Hap.

34:23.770 --> 34:25.025
[EXHALES SLOWLY]

34:25.051 --> 34:28.081
You saw what they did
to Leonard out there.

34:30.551 --> 34:32.574
All that damn time,

34:33.288 --> 34:37.089
during the '60s,
when we was protestin'...

34:38.860 --> 34:41.664
Look where it got us.
Goddamn nowhere.

34:41.829 --> 34:43.527
[SIGHS] What'd you think,

34:43.612 --> 34:46.333
painting them pictures
and smoking all that pot,

34:46.359 --> 34:48.426
think you'd change things around here?

34:49.248 --> 34:51.469
Yeah. Why not?

34:51.784 --> 34:53.810
I wasn't doing it for myself.

34:56.234 --> 34:57.738
You sure about that?

35:02.061 --> 35:03.630
[GUNSHOT, GLASS SHATTERS]

35:03.663 --> 35:06.931
[GUNFIRE]

35:08.134 --> 35:11.012
[GASPS]

35:11.871 --> 35:15.663
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

35:18.746 --> 35:19.777
Stay down!

35:20.114 --> 35:23.380
[GUNFIRE CONTINUES]

35:23.717 --> 35:27.425
[GRUNTING]

35:27.654 --> 35:30.425
♪♪

35:34.707 --> 35:35.791
LEONARD: Bacon.

35:36.659 --> 35:38.550
[GUNFIRE CONTINUES]

35:39.061 --> 35:41.202
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

35:42.418 --> 35:45.239
[GUNSHOTS]

35:45.271 --> 35:47.373
[WHISPERS] Toss it.

35:47.407 --> 35:50.778
♪♪

35:50.811 --> 35:52.647
- Uhh!
- SNEED: Bacon!

35:53.246 --> 35:55.116
Shit.
[GUNFIRE CONTINUES]

35:55.148 --> 35:57.996
♪♪

36:00.707 --> 36:02.676
- Whoo!
- Yeah!

36:02.710 --> 36:06.411
Say your prayers, assholes!
This is your last day on Earth.

36:06.504 --> 36:08.806
[GUNFIRE CONTINUES]

36:08.839 --> 36:10.608
Oh, shit!

36:14.473 --> 36:15.527
God!

36:18.548 --> 36:19.903
Sneed, cover me.

36:19.984 --> 36:22.721
[GUNSHOTS]

36:24.376 --> 36:25.711
HANSON: Come on.

36:26.089 --> 36:27.625
I'm fine. All right.

36:27.659 --> 36:30.035
♪♪

36:31.078 --> 36:32.579
Boone and Grady.

36:33.868 --> 36:35.267
Stay down!

36:36.183 --> 36:38.153
Boone! Grady!

36:38.984 --> 36:41.505
Just get in your truck and drive away.

36:41.538 --> 36:42.660
[GUNSHOT]
[LAUGHS]

36:42.686 --> 36:45.418
I'm telling you now, this is
not gonna end the way you want it to.

36:45.444 --> 36:47.434
BOONE: Yeah? We'll see!

36:47.779 --> 36:49.437
Last chance, boys.

36:50.323 --> 36:51.759
Get off this property!

36:52.059 --> 36:53.895
We came here to hunt some coon!

36:54.022 --> 36:55.784
That's what we gonna do.

36:56.042 --> 36:57.410
[GUNSHOTS]

36:57.583 --> 36:58.746
Sneed.

36:59.928 --> 37:01.589
On the count of three,

37:01.830 --> 37:03.727
shake that damn curtain.

37:04.666 --> 37:05.785
One...

37:07.169 --> 37:08.430
two...

37:09.472 --> 37:10.457
three!

37:11.374 --> 37:13.009
[GUNSHOTS]
[GLASS SHATTERS]

37:13.042 --> 37:15.297
Aah! Aah! Shit!

37:15.544 --> 37:16.646
♪♪

37:16.678 --> 37:18.855
[CRYING] Boone! Boone!
They shot me!

37:18.881 --> 37:19.864
You okay?

37:19.890 --> 37:22.213
No, I'm not okay, goddamn it!
They shot my eye out!

37:22.247 --> 37:25.102
Shut up, man. They shot
your eye. you'd be dead.

37:26.117 --> 37:28.160
♪♪

37:28.186 --> 37:30.719
They're gonna be. Pricks!

37:31.189 --> 37:32.957
♪♪

37:32.990 --> 37:35.253
[SIREN WAILING]

37:35.279 --> 37:37.660
Shit! Cantuck!
Let's go, man!

37:37.707 --> 37:39.975
Get us outta here! Let's go!
[POUNDS TRUCK]

37:40.008 --> 37:41.577
Move it, man! Get in the truck!

37:41.611 --> 37:43.613
[SIREN CONTINUES WAILING]
[ENGINE STARTS]

37:43.645 --> 37:46.649
♪♪

37:53.656 --> 37:55.692
♪♪

37:55.725 --> 37:58.902
MAN ON RADIO: <i> All units...
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]</i>

37:58.928 --> 38:02.765
<i>Reports of shots fired.
Request for backup.</i>

38:02.964 --> 38:05.934
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

38:05.968 --> 38:08.393
♪♪

38:09.872 --> 38:12.902
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

38:13.109 --> 38:16.112
♪♪

38:23.118 --> 38:25.020
♪♪

38:25.053 --> 38:26.588
[LIGHTS CLINK]

38:29.058 --> 38:32.929
[FLOORBOARDS CREAKING]

38:41.699 --> 38:44.707
[FRONT DOOR CREAKING]

38:45.380 --> 38:46.761
[FRONT DOOR CLOSES]

38:49.003 --> 38:50.823
Take it easy, boys.

38:59.821 --> 39:01.490
HAP: Sneed and Bacon?

39:01.524 --> 39:03.526
I got a little cabin
on a river up north.

39:03.558 --> 39:05.479
They'll be safe there.
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

39:05.795 --> 39:07.935
And what about Truman Brown?

39:08.397 --> 39:12.067
Is he gonna be... is he gonna
be chased outta town, too?

39:12.100 --> 39:13.681
I got a shitty job, Collins.

39:13.707 --> 39:16.401
Not many people around here
willing to do it.

39:16.769 --> 39:19.839
No, you won't find
much sympathy with me.

39:20.013 --> 39:22.683
I'm just saying, fixing
what's broken in this town

39:22.716 --> 39:24.218
is gonna take some time.

39:24.252 --> 39:26.955
Yeah, I-I got a lot of excuses

39:26.988 --> 39:29.524
for shitty things I don't wanna do, too.

39:29.556 --> 39:32.259
[CHUCKLES]
You sound like my wife.

39:32.292 --> 39:35.105
Well, she stuck around, huh?

39:35.131 --> 39:36.988
That so hard to believe?

39:37.265 --> 39:39.051
Kinda. Yeah.

39:39.077 --> 39:41.826
Shit. That's what
everybody says.

39:42.770 --> 39:44.372
Hey, you know, the only difference

39:44.404 --> 39:45.573
between a vulture and a woman

39:45.605 --> 39:47.508
is a vulture circles at least once

39:47.542 --> 39:49.746
before it chews your ass out.

39:49.877 --> 39:53.615
I'll be goddamned if that
ain't true about most women.

39:55.348 --> 39:56.848
But not my wife.

39:57.347 --> 39:58.551
Mnh-mnh.

39:58.910 --> 40:00.554
That's the truth.

40:01.399 --> 40:02.968
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

40:06.826 --> 40:07.962
[GRUNTS]

40:07.995 --> 40:09.931
You've given me something, Collins,

40:09.964 --> 40:12.941
I can use against Truman Brown
and his boys.

40:14.167 --> 40:15.464
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

40:15.490 --> 40:17.128
I'm gonna find your friend.

40:17.504 --> 40:18.972
That's a promise.

40:19.006 --> 40:21.206
[CAR DOOR OPENS]
When you find her,

40:21.875 --> 40:24.604
call me, day or night.

40:24.684 --> 40:25.824
Will do.

40:25.946 --> 40:28.230
♪♪

40:28.748 --> 40:31.652
It's best y'all don't come
around here for a good while,

40:31.685 --> 40:33.720
- at least.
- How 'bout never?

40:33.754 --> 40:36.524
- Hey, Collins.
- [GRUNTS] Yeah?

40:37.947 --> 40:39.198
Happy New Year.

40:39.365 --> 40:40.677
Mm.

40:47.006 --> 40:49.677
[ENGINE STARTS]

40:49.703 --> 40:51.539
[GEARS SHIFT]

40:54.442 --> 40:57.417
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

40:59.824 --> 41:03.074
[PEACEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

41:03.589 --> 41:05.453
[GUNSHOT]
[THUNDERCLAP]

41:05.486 --> 41:08.455
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

41:08.489 --> 41:11.493
♪♪

41:19.692 --> 41:23.230
